{"lemma":"شَخْصَيْ","slug":"شَخْصَيْ","root":"ش.خ.ص","root_slug":"ش-خ-ص","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-خ-ص","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":15},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21896","n21900"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%AE%D9%92%D8%B5%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to rise, to tower up"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become high, to become lofty"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to rise, to ascend"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to appear"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to stare, to gaze"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be glazed over"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to start out, to leave, to depart"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to travel, to journey"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pass"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to personify, to represent as a person, to represent as an individual"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to specify, to identify"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to act, to perform, to play (a part, role)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to diagnose (a disease)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"person, individual","examples":[{"text":"أَتَعْجَبُونَ مِنْ غَيْرَةِ سَعْدٍ؟ فَوَٱللَّٰهِ لَأَنَا أَغْيَرُ مِنْهُ، وَٱللَّهُ أَغْيَرُ مِنِّي، مِنْ أَجْلِ غَيْرَةِ اللَّهِ حَرَّمَ الْفَوَاحِشَ مَا ظَهَرَ مِنْهَا وَمَا بَطَنَ، وَلَا شَخْصَ أَغْيَرُ مِنَ اللَّهِ، وَلَا شَخْصَ أَحَبُّ إِلَيْهِ الْعُذْرُ مِنَ اللَّهِ، مِنْ أَجْلِ ذَلِكَ بَعَثَ اللَّهُ الْمُرْسَلِينَ مُبَشِّرِينَ وَمُنْذِرِينَ، وَلَا شَخْصَ أَحَبُّ إِلَيْهِ الْمِدْحَةُ مِنَ اللَّهِ، مِنْ أَجْلِ ذَلِكَ وَعَدَ اللَّهُ الْجَنَّةَ."},{"text":"فَكَانَ مِجَنِّي دُونَ مَنْ كُنْتُ أَتَّقِي / ثَلَاثَ شُخُوصٍ كَاعِبَانِ وَمُعْصِرُ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"figure, character"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʃa.xa.sˤa/","/ʃax.xa.sˤa/","/ʃaxsˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21896","headword_ar":"شَخَصَ","root":"$xS","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uxuwSN","text_ar":"شُخُوصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, rose;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became raised,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elevated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a star)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axaSa","text_ar":"شَخَصَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu $axoSN","text_ar":"لَهُ شَخْصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A figure seen from a distance rose to his view"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zwl","text_ar":"زول"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axaSa baSaruhu","text_ar":"شَخَصَ بَصَرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K, [in some copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baSarahu","text_ar":"بَصَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this occurs afterwards in that work,]) is said when a man opens his eyes and then does not move his eyelids; [and signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His eyes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his eye, became fixedly open:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K: *) or it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his eye became raised:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his sight became stretched and raised."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) [See the Kur xiv. 43, and xxi. 97.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axaSa","text_ar":"شَخَصَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayoka baSariY","text_ar":"اـِلَيْكَ بَصَرِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eyes, became fixedly open,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raised,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my sight became stretched and raised, towards thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axaSa baSaru Almay~iti","text_ar":"شَخَصَ بَصَرُ المَيِّتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) inf. n. as above, (IAth,) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eyes, of the dying man became fixedly open:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the eyelids of the dying man became raised upwards, and he looked intently, and became disquieted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disturbed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saxaSati Alkalimapu mina Alfami","text_ar":"سَخَصَتِ الكَلِمَةُ مِنَ الفَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The word,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sentence, rose"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the mouth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards the palate:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this is sometimes natural: i. e., one's raising his voice, and not being able to lower it. (K.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axaSa Als~ahomu","text_ar":"شَخَصَ السَّهْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(inf. n. as above, Msb,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The arrow rose"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to deviate"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the butt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"object of aim:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the arrow passed beyond the butt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"object of aim, going above it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose in the sky."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axaSa","text_ar":"شَخَصَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(aor. as above, Msb, and so the inf. n., S, Msb,) also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"from one town or country to another: (S, A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"from one place to another, (Msb,) or from his place of alighting or abiding: (TA:) or [so accord. to the TA, but in the K “ and ”]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he journeyed upwards."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axaSa mino qawomihi","text_ar":"شَخَصَ مِنْ قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went forth from his people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axaSa A_ilayohimo","text_ar":"شَخَصَ اـِلَيْهِمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he returned to them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-  Also, (M, K,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swelled;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became swollen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a wound)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose, and became swollen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, protuberant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prominent."},{"kind":"text","text":"]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axaSa baSarahu","text_ar":"شَخَصَ بَصَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axaSa bibaSarihi","text_ar":"شَخَصَ بِبَصَرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) or both, (TA, [in which it is said to be tropical,]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axaSa bibaSarihi A_ilaY","text_ar":"شَخَصَ بِبَصَرِهِ اـِلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amaA='i","text_ar":"السَّمَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axaSa","text_ar":"شَخَصَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[alone], (so in a copy of the A, [in which it is mentioned among proper expressions,]) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He raised his eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards the sky, and did not move his eyelids;"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a dying man: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he stretched and raised his sight:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he opened his eyes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and did not move his eyelids,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"looking fixedly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not moving his eyelids."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$oxaSu biSawotihi falaA yaqodiru EalaY","text_ar":"يَشْخَصُ بِصَوْتِهِ فَلَا يَقْدِرُ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xafoDihi","text_ar":"خَفْضِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He raises his voice, and is not able to lower it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uxiSa bihi","text_ar":"شُخِصَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) coordinate to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuniYa","text_ar":"عُنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uxiSa","text_ar":"شُخِصَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[alone], (so in a copy of the A,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axiSa bihi A^amorN","text_ar":"شَخِصَ بِهِ اَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", coordinate to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEiba","text_ar":"تَعِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axaSN","text_ar":"شَخَصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was disquieted by a thing that happened to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that disquieted him happened to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing happened to him and disquieted him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) as though he were raised from the ground by reason of his disquietude. (TA.) [See also 4.]       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axuSa","text_ar":"شَخُصَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axaASapN","text_ar":"شَخَاصَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or this is a simple subst., [for] ISd says, I have not heard a verb of which it may be the inf. n., (TA,) [if used, signifying]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, big, bulky,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corpulent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","IAth","TA","M","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n21900","headword_ar":"شَخْصٌ","root":"$xS","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"body,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bodily"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corporeal form"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"figure"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"substance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAd","text_ar":"سَوَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"some other object"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which one sees from a distance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K:) applying in common to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juv~apN","text_ar":"جُثَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TalalN","text_ar":"طَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in relation to a man;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in relation to a man sitting"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sleeping"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lying down"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in relation to a man standing erect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juv~apN","text_ar":"جُثَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or it is applied only to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a body,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"material substance, composed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not simple,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and having height:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Khattábee, Msb, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any body,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"material thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"substance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is somewhat high, and conspicuous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having height and appearance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA:) pl. (of pauc., S)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oxuSN","text_ar":"اَشْخُصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and (of mult., S)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oxaASN","text_ar":"اَشْخَاصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is properly another pl. of pauc.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uxuwSN","text_ar":"شُخُوصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ixaASN","text_ar":"شِخَاصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  Then used as signifying (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man himself; a man's self,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"person; his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAt","text_ar":"ذَات"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) [i. e.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person; a being; an individual;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafosN","text_ar":"نَفْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[also syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtN","text_ar":"ذَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (L, TA;) as in the following verse of 'Amr Ibn-Rabee'ah, cited by Sb:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"fakaAna mijan~iY duwna mano kunotu A^at~aqiY\n                      \n                     \n                        valaAvu $uxuwSK kaAEibaAni wamuEoSiru"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And three persons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two girls whose breasts were beginning to swell and one who had attained the age of puberty, were my shield against such as I was fearing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAvapu","text_ar":"ثَلَاثَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anofusK","text_ar":"اَنْفُسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) [the poet making the word in question fem. because it relates here to females: but] Rubeh is related to have said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAvapu A^a$oxuSK","text_ar":"ثَلَاثَةُ اَشْخُصٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, of women. (M, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafosN","text_ar":"نَفْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axoS","text_ar":"شَخْص"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person"},{"kind":"text","text":"] ceases to be a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$xS","text_ar":"شخص"},{"kind":"text","text":"by its being divided; whereas, when a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jisom","text_ar":"جِسْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is divided, no part of it ceases to be a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jsm","text_ar":"جسم"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Er-Rághib, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jsm","text_ar":"جسم"},{"kind":"text","text":".) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA $axoSa A^agoyaru mina A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"لَا شَخْصَ اَغْيَرُ مِنَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not any being more jealous than God"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$xS","text_ar":"شخص"},{"kind":"text","text":"being here metaphorically used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAt","text_ar":"ذَات"},{"kind":"text","text":": or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$xS","text_ar":"شخص"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"should not be more jealous than God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but accord. to one relation, the words are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA $aYo'a A^agoyaru mina A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"لَا شَىْءَ اَغْيَرُ مِنَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which has the first of the two meanings mentioned above]. (IAth, TA.) [It is also used in a pl. sense: see a verse of Ziyád el-Aajam in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlY","text_ar":"الى"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","IAth","TA","L"]}]}}